Redesign secondary widgets as 4-column grid with smart span packing

Replace the 2-column currency+omni layout with a unified 4-column grid
system. All items (currency and omni extras) are rendered as uniform
grid cells with JS-computed column spans based on content weight.

- 4-column grid, items pack into rows of 4 columns
- Each item gets a weight: short text (1), medium (2), long (3),
  currency (2) — spans are assigned proportionally
- Remaining columns in a row are distributed to heaviest items
- Rows overflow naturally when items exceed 4 columns
- Currency is now a compact inline cell (emoji + coin values)
- Removed old dnd-currency-widget/dnd-omni-widgets template markup;
  everything is rendered dynamically by renderSecondaryGrid()
